6.10	Smith_%26_Wesson_Model_1	Smith &amp; Wesson Model 1	The Smith &amp; Wesson Model 1 was the first firearm manufactured by Smith &amp; Wesson, with production commencing in 1857. It was also the first commercially available revolver to use rimfire cartridges instead of loose powder, musket ball, and percussion caps. It is a single-action, tip-up revolver holding 7 .22 Short cartridges.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/bc/Smith-et-Wesson-model-1-22-p1030158.jpg/300px-Smith-et-Wesson-model-1-22-p1030158.jpg
